Lunarpine grins a toothy grin, &quot;Front line combat? I wouldn&#39;t have it any
other way.&quot; he catches the cloaking device and attaches it to his side. He
wanted the front line, hopefully he&#39;d get the first scent if there was any
trouble. He felt some sort of loyalty toward Ceratis that made him want to
reject the cloaking device and fight straight up. If Striker was still under
enemy influence the devices were a waste of time to begin with. If Striker
was under enemy control then Lunarpine felt an obligation to help him.
Striker was one of the only two wolves he knew existed in this war. &quot;The
Pack must survive.&quot; he thought as he prepared for battle.

He exits rhe Ark at Ramulus&#39; side, being slightly taller makes Lunarpine
look like a body gaurd. (How many cloaked bots are going into battle?) The
scents of thier friends were all around them . He hoped to get to the
captive Maximals before any mech fluid was shed. he knew it was wishful
thinking even with his new speed. One thing had to be adressed, &quot;What if...&quot;
He turned to Ramulus dreading the inevitable answer &quot;What if thesetrainers
found a way to change Spears and Strikers command codes?&quot;
